  year={2022},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={1-6},
  abstract={The European interconnected grid is an association of all transmission system operators from Europe and enables a stable grid frequency and high security of supply. Due to the increasing share of volatile, decentralised renewable energies and the promotion of electromobility, the grid operators of the transmission and distribution grids are facing new challenges among others in the operational management of the electrical grid. To be able to train future engineers and students for this challenging grid operation and to train employees of grid operators, practical, realistic experience is essential in addition to theoretical knowledge. Since incorrect switching operations on the real grid can have serious consequences, it is necessary to set up a simulation of a grid control station for this purpose. Current service providers train employees in special simulators. However, the use of these simulators is strictly limited to fixed dates. In addition, the participation of prospective engineers as students is often not accessible due to the high costs involved in theses training sessions. Therefore, this paper describes a grid control station in virtual reality. Real grids are represented as a digital twin and are integrated into the virtual reality control station. However, the coupling of these two components currently exists only as a concept but will be realised soon. The participants immerse into the virtual grid control station, perform switching actions in different scenarios, and experience the consequences of their actions to increase their practical knowledge in grid operations to face the future grid challenges. The VR grid control station is to be offered as an education opportunity in the field of power engineering at Bielefeld University of Applied Sciences.},
