  abstract={The accounting informatization course for applied undergraduate accounting majors is to train students into practical accounting talents who can adapt to the current information environment. By analyzing the importance of the construction of accounting informatization course and its teaching status, combined with the training of applied undergraduate accounting professionals in our college, the course system and course content are analyzed. Suggestions such as the integration of disciplines with artificial intelligence and other information technologies. Real-time mapping and real-time interaction between the physical accounting professional entity and the digital accounting professional twin are realized by constructing the accounting professional digital twin model (MDTM). Focusing on the construction goals of the smart accounting profession, focusing on the system construction, optimization and key technologies of the smart accounting profession, digital twins and deep learning methods based on the cyber-physical space of the accounting profession.},
