  abstract={Growing number of new building in recent years has led to increased installation of firefighting systems that require safety inspections. This has resulted in shortage of firefighting equipment safety inspection manpower and need for a digitized data management system for efficient inspections and post-inspection management. That is, periodic inspections of firefighting equipment installed in building are absolutely necessary for safety against fire and this study proposes some technological improvements for firefighting equipment inspections. In particular, augmented reality and cognitive intelligence are combined in a firefighting equipment inspection system and wearable devices are used to boost easiness and quality of inspections. Furthermore, the proposed system aims for not only the firefighting experts but the general public to have convenient access to learn more easily about fire prevention and firefighting inspection system.},
