  abstract={Under the background of “Internet +” era, with the continuous progress of science and technology, the public has diversified requirements for museum visiting experience. The experience mode of both artistic taste and participation has become the development trend of Museum guidance. This paper discusses the application of interactive design based on BP neural network in Museum navigation. In this project, we use BP neural network to predict the user's next destination from the user's current location, and then display it on the map. BP neural network is used to predict the next destination according to the user's current location, and then display it on the map. BP neural network can be used as an intelligent system to identify objects or people by viewing images or videos. It is one of the most popular technologies because it has many advantages over other machine learning technologies (such as supervised and unsupervised learning methods), which cannot process video data. In this paper, the user behavior of visitors is collected by means of on-site research, structured interview, case tracking, online research, etc., and the user model of museum visitors is obtained through analysis and research, which provides the basis of user experience for practical design. By analyzing the cognitive characteristics of indoor geographic space, the principles of indoor map design are summarized, and the guiding principles for indoor navigation products of museums are obtained by considering the special scenes of museums, the needs of visitors and other factors.},
